    Online Casino Bonus types

    How to choose your casino bonus

    â€‹

    If the first question is what casino to choose, the following one will always be which casino bonus or welcome package to opt for. Without doubt you can easily find hundred of bonuses, free spins and exclusive promotions on internet, but how do you find the best offer and bonus requirements? Whether you're a new player or an experienced one, it's always a good idea to get some extra cash to play with and boost your balance, considering those are quite easy to claim. Below you will find an overview of all possible bonuses you can collect from the different online casinos, as well as the general requirements to claim the bonus or offer.  In most cases, the standard formula is: deposit 100, get extra 100, wager x times, withdraw.

     

    Always have a look at the Terms and Condition page, check what the requirement are, and pay attention to Wager, max bonus bet and maximum withdraw amount

    â€‹

    â€‹

    Deposit Bonus with Wager

     

    Without doubt this is the most common welcome bonus an online casino can offer to a new registered player. In short, you will get an extra 50% to 100% of the amount of your first deposit, which will allow your to start playing with a higher balance, however you're not getting it for free. Like most bonuses, there are some requirements included in order to qualify for this type of bonus. Firstly you will need to wager you deposited amount, on average, 25 to 45 times and until then,  you won't be able to withdraw your money. On the side note, this doesn't apply exclusively to new players; the wagering requirements apply to existing players as well. When this type of bonus is given to an existing and experienced player, it's a gesture done by casino to thank the player for choosing them over and over again, and of course, to keep the player motivated in choosing them in the future. No matter if you're new or experienced player, before selecting this or any other kind of bonus, we always highly advise to carefully read the Terms & Conditions page.

    â€‹

    â€‹

    Deposit Bonus Wager Free

     

    This is what come may call a ''unicorn bonus'' since it's so rare - many don't believe they exist but some swear they've seen it. The reason why some players after registering in a new online casino don't select any bonus is because of the wagering requirement, since in a lot of casinos it can be quite high, even up to 45x, however the amount of casinos that offer 100% bonus on deposit with no wagering requirement is extremely rare. We always recommend to read the T&C's page since you might need to wager at least 1x your initial deposit. Deposit bonus which is wager free is definitely the dream of any player - deposit €100 and get extra €100 for free - a good way to boost your balance and play longer your favorite slots.

    No Deposit Bonus

    â€‹

    With no deposit bonus we refer to all bonuses that don't require any deposit. Some may say that this type of bonus is one the most attractive bonuses for players, mostly to first-time players, who want to try out games in a new casino, possibly winning some extra cash, with zero risk. A no deposit bonus can be cash money, free spins or bonus spins, whichever of these three option you get, you have guaranteed fun for free. In our opinion, this is the most soft approach to online gambling.

    Welcome Bonus / Sign up Bonus

     

    A welcome bonus or a sign up bonus is definitely the most common way a casino thanks its' new player for choosing them. These type of bonuses are valid only for new players upon their registration/account creation. In some casinos you may find the welcome bonus as a package including free spins, however as attractive the welcome bonus or the package may look like, in majority of casinos there are specific requirements in place before withdrawing your funds. Again, we highly recommend to carefully read the Terms and Conditions for this specific bonus before using it, to go through all requirements and avoid any misunderstandings. Sometimes a specific code will be required in order to get the welcome bonus. Lastly, if you notice that your welcome bonus is being ''stretched-out'' to 2-4 first deposits, in that case you've definitely got a welcome package in your hands.

    Reload Bonus

     

    A reload bonus can be considered as an incentive to make further deposits after the initial one, which, in a way, is an extension of a welcome bonus just on a smaller scale. These bonuses are never the same and differ from casino to casino. In other words, a reload bonus is a way a casino keeps players entertained, happy and also loyal to them. Keep in mind that in most cases these bonuses can be claimed within a certain time frame and may have different requirements than a welcome bonus.

    Cashback Bonus

     

    Imagine a casino where you make a deposit, start playing and have fun though after a while you finish your money, but the online casino gives part of your money back to you. Well, guess what, this is not a dream, it's called a cashback bonus and is a fairly common bonus offered by casinos. A Cashback bonus does exactly what it says it does - it gives you back a percentage of the amount you've lost. The percentage and frequency depends on the casino - they may have it on weekly basis, or, for example, weekend losses only. In most cases the casino will refund you between 5% and 25% 

    Free Spin

     

    Free Spin (also called Cash Spin) are generally part of the welcome package or as no deposit bonus. The player can use free spin given by casino to play his/her favorite games without spending his/her own money.  Apart from getting your free spin as a welcome package, occasionally some casinos can use free spin as a reward for players when, for example, they have collected a certain amount of points (we refer to this as point scheme) or simply for being loyal to the casino. According to UKGC guidelines, casinos are required to advertise free spin as bonus spin with wagering requirements included.
